FuncDef: This command renumbers existing MRP policy entries to properly sequence policy entries. This may be required in some cases since the implementation exits when the first match is found and executes the actions according to the accompanying action command. This requires that entries be sequenced correctly from most to least explicit.

ParaDef.Info: Specifies the entry number of an existing entry. Values-1 to 65535.
Specifies the new entry number to be assigned to the old entry. If the new entry exists, an error message is generated. Values-1 to 65535.
